title: MUSA 5080 Portfolio
text:
This portfolio documents my learning journey in Public Policy Analytics (MUSA 5080).


Advanced spatial analysis and data science for urban planning and public policy.




Weekly Notes: My learning reflections and key concepts
Labs: Completed assignments and analyses
Final Project: Capstone modeling challenge




My name is Wil Rantala. I’m from Chicago and got my BA in Environment and Development from McGill University. Currently, I am pursuing my Master of City Planning at the University of Pennsylvania with a concentration in Transportation Planning. I’m taking this course to advance my data science skills to be a more rounded, technical professional in the planning world. Mainly, I want to feel comfortable in R!




Email: wrantala@upenn.edu
GitHub: @wrantala11
